Module com.example.gymmembershipgui
Package com.example.gymmembershipgui

Class MemberDatabase

java.lang.Object
com.example.gymmembershipgui.MemberDatabase
public class MemberDatabase extends Object
MemberDatabase manages the members at a gym, or in a fitness class. Each database is defined with an array of members as well as a size of the database. Members can be found in the database by comparing each member in the database to the member that needs to be found. Additionally, when the database has reached capacity and more members need to be added, the database can grow in size. If a member wants to join the gym, they can be added to the database, and if a member would like to leave, they can be removed. The database can also sort the members by name, location, expiration date, fee and display the members in the database.
Author:
Arunima Tripathy, Mahfuza Rahman

  • Constructor Details

    • MemberDatabase

      public MemberDatabase()
      Creates an instance of MemberDatabase with a list of members and size. Creates an array of length four and sets the size of database to 0. The size represents the number of members in the array and the index the next member should be added to.

    • find

      private int find(Member member)
      Finds the index number at which a member exists in the list of members. Iterates through array of members, and checks if an existing member equals the member passed as a parameter.
      Parameters:
      member - the member that must be found.
      Returns:
      the index the member is at in list of members, -1 if not found.

    • grow

      private void grow()
      Increases the size of database when the array is filled to capacity. Creates a new array with the length of the list of members plus 4. Copies the members of the original array of members to the new array. Sets the old array of members to equal to the new array of members.

    • add

      public boolean add(Member member)
      Adds a member to the database. If array of members is filled, database is grown. Checks if member already exists in the database. If member does not exist, then the member is added, and size is grown. Otherwise, member is not added.
      Parameters:
      member - the member that is being added to the database.
      Returns:
      true if member is added, false if member in database already.

    • remove

      public boolean remove(Member member)
      Removes a member from the database. Checks if member exists in the database. If member exists, the member is removed from the list of members, and following members are moved to left of list, and size is decreased.
      Parameters:
      member - the member that must be removed.
      Returns:
      true if member removed, false if the member is not in database.

    • print

      public String print()
      Displays the list of members in database. Iterates through the list of members and prints each member.
      Returns:
      a String containing all the members in the database.

    • printByCounty

      Displays the list of members in database ordered by county and zipcode. Sorts the list by county and zip code using in-place insertion sort. Iterates through the list of members and prints each member.
      Returns:

    • printByExpirationDate

      public String printByExpirationDate()
      Displays the list of members in database ordered by expiration date. Sorts the list by membership expiration using in-place insertion sort. Iterates through the list of members and prints each member.
      Returns:
      a String containing all the members in the database ordered by expiration date.

    • printByName

      public String printByName()
      Displays the list of members in database ordered last and first name. Sorts the list by last and then first name using in-place insertion sort. Iterates through the list of members and prints each member.
      Returns:
      a String containing all the members in the database ordered by their last and first names.

    • printByMembershipFee

      public String printByMembershipFee()
      Displays the list of members in database with their membership fees. Sorts the list by membership fees using in-place insertion sort. Iterates through the list of members and prints each member.
      Returns:
      a String containing all the members in the database along with their membership fees.
